cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is about fine-grained image recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel end-to-end model, which involves selecting useful and meaningful convolutional descriptors, indicating that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are also relevant sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) to some extent.
